ğŸ‘‰ Tasks running in any AZ will share the same data in the EFS file system
ğŸ‘‰ Fargate + EFS = Serverless
ğŸ‘‰ Use cases: persistent multi-AZ shared storage for your containers
ğŸ‘‰ Amazon S3 cannot be mounted as a file system

Hello Connections ğŸ‘‹ What is ECS â€“Task Definitions?
ğŸ¯ğ——ğ—®ğ˜† ğŸğŸ ğ‡ğšğ§ğğ¬-ğ¨ğ§ ğğğğ© ğğ¢ğ¯ğ ğ€ğ–ğ’ #100daysofcloud challenge
ğŸ ğœğ¨ğ§ğœğğ©ğ­ ğš ğğšğ² ğğªğ®ğšğ¥ğ¬ ğŸ‘ğŸ”ğŸ“ ğœğ¨ğ§ğœğğ©ğ­ğ¬ = ğŸ” ğ­ğğœğ¡ğ§ğ¢ğœğšğ¥ ğœğğ«ğ­ğ¢ğŸğ¢ğœğšğ­ğ¢ğ¨ğ§ğ¬

ğ€ğ¦ğšğ³ğ¨ğ§ ğ„ğ‚ğ’ â€“ğ“ğšğ¬ğ¤ ğƒğğŸğ¢ğ§ğ¢ğ­ğ¢ğ¨ğ§ğ¬:
ğŸ‘‰ Task definitions are metadata in JSON form to tell ECS how to run a Docker container.
ğŸ‘‰ Can define up to 10 containers in a Task Definition.
ğŸ‘‰ It contains crucial information, such as: Image Name, Port Binding for Container and Host, Memory and CPU required, Environment variables, Networking information, IAM Role, Logging configuration (ex CloudWatch).

ğ€ğ¦ğšğ³ğ¨ğ§ ğ„ğ‚ğ’ â€“ ğ„ğ§ğ¯ğ¢ğ«ğ¨ğ§ğ¦ğğ§ğ­ ğ•ğšğ«ğ¢ğšğ›ğ¥ğğ¬:
ğŸ‘‰ Environment Variables for task can be fetched from Hardcoded â€“ e.g., URLs, SSM Parameter Store â€“ sensitive variables (e.g., API keys, shared configs), Secrets Manager â€“ sensitive variables (e.g., DB passwords), Amazon S3 â€“ e.g., bulk files.

ğ€ğ¦ğšğ³ğ¨ğ§ ğ„ğ‚ğ’ â€“ğ“ğšğ¬ğ¤ ğğ¥ğšğœğğ¦ğğ§ğ­:
ğŸ‘‰When an ECS task is started with EC2 Launch Type, ECS must determine where to place it, with the constraints of CPU and memory (RAM).
ğŸ‘‰Task Placement Strategies- Binpack tasks are placed on the least available amount of CPU and Memory, Random tasks are placed randomly, Spread tasks are placed evenly based on the specified value.
ğŸ‘‰Task Placement Constraints- DistinctInstance tasks are placed on a different EC2 instance, MemberOf tasks are placed on EC2 instances that satisfy a specified expression.


ğ‡ğğ¥ğ¥ğ¨ ğ‚ğ¨ğ§ğ§ğğœğ­ğ¢ğ¨ğ§ğ¬ ğŸ‘‹ ğ–ğ¡ğšğ­ ğ¢ğ¬ ğ’ğ¢ğ¦ğ©ğ¥ğ ğğ®ğğ®ğ ğ’ğğ«ğ¯ğ¢ğœğ ?
ğŸ¯ğ——ğ—®ğ˜† ğŸğŸ ğ€ğ–ğ’ #100daysofcloud
 
ğ€ğ¦ğšğ³ğ¨ğ§ ğ’ğğ’:
ğŸ‘‰ Simple Queue Service  is fully managed service used to decouple applications.
ğŸ‘‰ Producer sends message to >SQS > consumer polls the message.
ğŸ‘‰ It is asynchronous based, limitation of 256KB per message sent.
ğŸ‘‰ Message is persisted in SQS until a consumer deletes it.
ğŸ‘‰ Consumers Process in (running on EC2 instances, servers, or AWS Lambda..etc)
ğŸ‘‰ SQS with auto scaling group can be created using- cloud watch metric & alarm.
ğŸ‘‰ SQS Security- Encryption (https, kms key) / iam policy/ access policy.
ğŸ‘‰ Message Visibility Timeout - message becomes invisible to other consumers.
ğŸ‘‰ SQS First In First Out is ordering of messages in the queue.
ğŸ‘‰ Dead Letter Queue- after the maximum receives threshold is exceeded, the message goes into it.
ğŸ‘‰ Using the SQS Extended Client we can send large messages e.g. 1GB.


